{"_id":"77ef411dfea71718","name":"Golden Heart-Shaped Necklace","type":"clue","img":"icons/equipment/neck/necklace-gold-heart.webp","system":{"description":"A golden heart-shaped necklace that Princess Tuvstarr lost in the black pond in the depths of the woods, according to the original fairy tale by Helge Kjellin. This precious piece of jewelry represents Tuvstarr's final connection to her old life before she plunged her heart and soul into the black water to enter the Dream World. The necklace symbolizes the innocent heart of the Princess before she was consumed by her wish for a perfect world.","location":"Lost in the black pond (original fairy tale)","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"tuvstarrs-reflection"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"fe5727d82eaba6d1","name":"Knightly Plate Armor at Pond Bottom","type":"clue","img":"icons/equipment/chest/breastplate-scale-steel.webp","system":{"description":"A knight's plate armor lying at the bottom of the black pond, visible in Tuvstarr's reflection. The shield bears a fox with two tails as heraldic symbol, matching the crest that can be found in the forest. This armor belonged to the Gallant Knight who entered the Dream World before the Hunters arrived. Footsteps on the muddy shore lead from this armor into the black water, marking the path between the real world and the Dream World. The armor serves as evidence that knights have been here and provides a crucial link to understanding how to reach Tuvstarr.","location":"Bottom of the black pond (visible in reflection)","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"tuvstarrs-reflection"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"0f5356f1d48cb6a5","name":"Knight's Crest with Two-Tailed Fox","type":"clue","img":"icons/sundries/gaming/shield-heraldry-gray-red.webp","system":{"description":"A knightly crest bearing the heraldic symbol of a fox with two tails. This crest belonged to one of the fallen knights who died searching for Princess Tuvstarr in the corrupted forest. The crest can be found on the body of the knight's dead warhorse or near his plate armor at the bottom of the black pond. Showing this crest to the Gallant Knight proves that his brothers-in-arms all perished in the search, and can convince him to abandon his comfortable exile in the Dream World and resume his quest to save the kingdom.","location":"Dead knight's body in the forest or armor near black pond","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"tuvstarrs-reflection"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"f76b1734b10d7e1c","name":"Lance of the Fallen Knight","type":"object","img":"icons/weapons/polearms/spear-hooked-steel.webp","system":{"description":"An ashwood spear with an iron point that belonged to one of the knights sent by the King and Queen to find Princess Tuvstarr. The knight lies dead near a dark pond, his eyes white and puffy like a sack of eggs ready to burst. This lance was the weapon that mortally wounded Skutt the moose, though the beast could not truly die due to Tuvstarr's wish. The tip of the lance can ignite at will, casting light and providing a burning fire always at hand. When wielded with skill, it can inflict additional wounds on enemies.","quantity":1,"weight":5,"value":400,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical","Ignites on command","Enhanced damage","Knight's weapon","Two-handed"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"8c7db1389ebf64c2","name":"Tuvstarr's Golden Crown","type":"object","img":"icons/equipment/head/crown-gold-jeweled-ruby.webp","system":{"description":"A small golden crown that once belonged to Princess Tuvstarr, now sitting on a small islet in an open swamp. The crown shines bright as a small sun, and its light has corrupted the Fairies who dance around it in an eternal trance. Tuvstarr traded this crown with the Fairies to gain safe passage across the swamp on her journey to the black pond. The crown's magical light draws both fascination and madness to those who gaze upon it.","quantity":1,"weight":2,"value":1500,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical","Royal artifact","Corrupting light","Fairy-enchanted","Tuvstarr's memory trigger"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"4501d48456b19c68","name":"Tuvstarr's Reflection in the Black Pond","type":"clue","img":"icons/magic/water/water-hand-glow.webp","system":{"description":"While Princess Tuvstarr is gone from the real world, her reflection can still be seen in the black waters of the pond at the center of the forest. The reflection shows an image of a naked girl sitting on the shore and staring into the abyss. Next to her reflection is a knight's plate armor with a shield bearing a fox with two tails as heraldic symbol. Footsteps on the muddy shore lead into the black water. This reflection is the gateway between the real world and the Dream World that Tuvstarr created with her wish.","location":"The black pond at the center of the great forest","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"tuvstarrs-reflection"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"6ccf36c5df7b9590","name":"Tuvstarr's White Dress","type":"object","img":"icons/equipment/chest/dress-layered-silk-white.webp","system":{"description":"Princess Tuvstarr's elegant white dress, traded to the Hulder (a forest spirit) in exchange for safe passage through the dark woods. The dress made the Hulder feel beautiful and strong, but also awakened a voracious hunger that corrupted her into a grotesque monster. The Hulder now wears the dress as a dirty blindfold over her eyes, obsessively repeating how beautiful and graceful she is, unaware of what she has become. When Tuvstarr holds this dress again, she can feel the warmth of its fabric and remember the weight of reality.","quantity":1,"weight":1,"value":500,"equipped":false,"properties":["Magical","Royal garment","Corrupting influence","Memory trigger","Spirit-touched"]},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
